paper_metadata.title: MAIN TEXT
paper_metadata.extraction_summary: The paper discusses various single nucleotide polymorphisms (SNPs) in the TTR gene and their association with Lewy body disorders, but does not provide specific penetrance data for individual carriers.

functional_data.summary: The SNP is located in exon 2 and leads to a non-synonymous amino acid exchange.

variants.additional_notes: No significant associations with LBD occurrence were found for this SNP.
key_quotes: None of the analyzed TTR SNPs (rs723744, rs13381522, rs3764478, rs1800458 and rs36204272) showed a significant association with LBD occurrence.

functional_data.summary: This SNP is located in intron 3 and does not result in amino acid differences.

functional_data.summary: This SNP is intronic and spliced posttranslationally, should have no effect on the TTR protein.
